This metrical irregularity ( SLSL in the second foot) is not uncommon in pre-Islamic and early Islamic verse but rare in later periods. The verb sanna and the following noun sanan allude to the related word Sunnah . Instead of sananta , Wāfī has sannayta (‘you opened, have facilitated’), probably an attempt to regularise the metre.
