list.item:
Mensuration (
K. al-misāḥah
).

On medicine (
K. fī l-ṭibb
), dedicated to al-Malik al-Muʾayyad Najm al-Dīn Masʿūd, the son of al-Malik al-Nāṣir Ṣalāḥ al-Dīn Yūsuf ibn Ayyūb; in it the author summarizes the generalities of the art of medicine and his knowledge of diseases, their causes and remedies.

On market medicine (
K. ṭibb al-sūq
), dedicated to one of his disciples, in which the author mentions the diseases that occur frequently and their treatment by medicaments that are easily accessible and well-known.

On the reason why mountains were created
(M. fī al-sabab alladhī lahu khuliqat al-jibāl
), dedicated to al-Malik al-Amjad.

On the elements (
K. al-usṭuqussāt
).

Marginal notes and experiences in medicine (
Taʿālīq wa-mujarrabāt fī l-ṭibb
).

On the temperament of al-Raqqah (
M. fī mizāj al-Raqqah
).

Entertaining anecdotes on medicine (
K. al-mulaḥ fī ṭibb
). In this work, the author mentions many excellent matters and useful facts from the works of Galen and other authors.

The precise book on combining and dividing, in which he mentions the diseases, their similarities and the differences between each of them in most cases (
K. al-tadqīq fī l-jamʿ wa-l-tafrīq
).

Explanatory remarks with regard to the results of his experiences and the like (
Taʿālīq mā ḥaṣala lahu min al-tajārib wa-ghayrihā
).

Commentary on the prophetic traditions dealing with medical matters (
Sharḥ aḥādīth nabawiyyah tataʿallaqu bi-l-ṭibb
).

Introduction to medicine (
K. al-mudkhal ilā l-ṭibb
).

On causes and accidents (
K. al-ʿilal wa-l-aʿrāḍ
).

Guide to simple drugs (
K. al-ishārāt al-murshidah fī l-adwiyah al-mufradah
).

The Brilliant Book: on jewels (
K. al-bāhir fī l-jawāhir
).

